---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="For Marketing Directors - Waterloo Track" description="Turn data chaos into boardroom confidence. Get attribution that finance actually trusts.">
	<main>
		<!-- Hero Section -->
		<section class="hero">
			<div class="container">
				<h1>Your CEO Wants to Know:<br>"Which Marketing Actually Works?"</h1>
				<p>And you're presenting attribution data that even you don't fully trust. Time to get numbers that make sense to finance.</p>
				<a href="#solution" class="btn">Get Boardroom-Ready Data</a>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Career Problem Section -->
		<section class="section">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>The Career-Limiting Truth About Marketing Attribution</h2>
				<p>You walk into the boardroom with charts that show marketing is "driving results." But the CFO is looking at you like you're speaking a foreign language.</p>
				
				<div style="background: #f8f9fa; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 30px 0;">
					<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2;">The questions you can't confidently answer:</h3>
					<ul style="padding-left: 20px; line-height: 1.8; margin-top: 15px;">
						<li>"Which campaigns drove the revenue spike in Q3?"</li>
						<li>"Why are we spending more on ads but seeing lower ROAS?"</li>
						<li>"Can you prove marketing caused that $200k deal?"</li>
						<li>"What happens if we cut the Google Ads budget in half?"</li>
						<li>"Which marketing channels deserve more budget next quarter?"</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				
				<p><strong>The real problem:</strong> Your attribution data is incomplete, inconsistent, and impossible to validate. And everyone in that boardroom knows it.</p>
				
				<div style="background: #333; color: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 30px 0; text-align: center;">
					<p style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 15px;">Marketing directors with unreliable attribution data are 60% more likely to lose budget in economic downturns.</p>
					<p style="color: #eed36b; font-weight: 600;">When cuts come, marketing gets hit first—unless you can prove your value.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Data Chaos Section -->
		<section class="section section-alt">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>The Data Nightmare You're Managing</h2>
				<p>Every platform tells a different story. Every report contradicts the last one. And you're supposed to make strategic decisions from this chaos.</p>
				
				<div style="display: grid; gap: 30px; margin: 40px 0;">
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #eed36b;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2;">Platform Wars</h3>
						<p>Facebook claims credit for $100k in revenue. Google says they drove $80k. Your CRM shows $150k total. Somehow marketing "generated" $280k from $150k in actual revenue.</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #eed36b;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2;">The Attribution Black Hole</h3>
						<p>30% of your conversions are "direct" or "organic" in your analytics. But you know a chunk of those came from ads that platforms can't track anymore.</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #eed36b;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2;">Reporting Theatre</h3>
						<p>You spend hours every week creating reports that look impressive but can't answer the basic question: "What should we do differently?"</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				
				<p style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 2rem;">You're not running marketing. You're running a data reconciliation department.</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Solution Section -->
		<section id="solution" class="section">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>What If Your Attribution Data Actually Made Sense?</h2>
				<p>Imagine walking into the next board meeting with numbers that align. Revenue that adds up. Attribution that finance trusts.</p>
				
				<div style="display: grid; gap: 40px; margin: 40px 0; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));">
					<div style="background: #f8f9fa; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2;">Single Source of Truth</h3>
						<p>All revenue gets tracked to the original source. No more platform wars. No more impossible math. Just clean, auditable data.</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="background: #f8f9fa; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2;">Finance-Grade Reports</h3>
						<p>Attribution data that ties to actual revenue. Every dollar tracked. Every conversion documented. Numbers your CFO will actually believe.</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="background: #f8f9fa; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2;">Strategic Clarity</h3>
						<p>Stop guessing which channels to invest in. See exactly where each dollar of marketing budget drives the highest return.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				
				<div style="text-align: center; background: #7cd3d2; color: white; padding: 40px; border-radius: 8px; margin-top: 40px;">
					<p style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Result:</strong></p>
					<p style="font-size: 1.25rem;">You become the marketing leader who can prove ROI, justify budget, and drive profitable growth.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Competitive Advantage Section -->
		<section class="section section-alt">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>The Strategic Advantage of Real Attribution</h2>
				<p>While your competitors are still arguing about which platform deserves credit, you're making data-driven decisions that compound over time.</p>
				
				<div style="display: grid; gap: 30px; margin: 40px 0;">
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2;">Budget Optimization</h3>
						<p>Reallocate budget from underperforming channels to high-ROI campaigns. Most marketing teams find 20-30% efficiency gains immediately.</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2;">Executive Confidence</h3>
						<p>Present data that leadership actually trusts. No more defending your budget or explaining why the numbers don't add up.</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2;">Strategic Planning</h3>
						<p>Make growth plans based on actual performance, not platform promises. Build marketing strategies that scale profitably.</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2;">Team Productivity</h3>
						<p>Stop spending hours reconciling conflicting reports. Invest that time in strategy and optimization instead.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Success Stories Section -->
		<section class="section">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>Marketing Leaders Who Transformed Their Data</h2>
				<p>These aren't fluffy case studies. They're marketing directors who were tired of presenting data they couldn't defend.</p>
				
				<div style="display: grid; gap: 30px; margin-top: 40px;">
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #7cd3d2;">
						<p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 20px; font-style: italic;">"First board meeting after implementation: every number tied to actual revenue. CFO said it was the clearest marketing report they'd ever seen. Got approval for 40% budget increase on the spot."</p>
						<p style="font-weight: 600;">Marketing Director, B2B SaaS</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #7cd3d2;">
						<p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 20px; font-style: italic;">"Discovered three channels that looked profitable were actually losing money. Reallocated $50k/month budget to channels with real ROI. Marketing efficiency up 60% in one quarter."</p>
						<p style="font-weight: 600;">VP Marketing, E-commerce</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #7cd3d2;">
						<p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 20px; font-style: italic;">"Finally had attribution data I could stake my reputation on. When the CEO asked which campaigns to cut during budget freezes, I had clear answers backed by real data."</p>
						<p style="font-weight: 600;">Director of Growth</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- ROI Section -->
		<section class="section section-alt">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>The ROI That Actually Matters</h2>
				<p>This isn't about marketing ROI. This is about career ROI. The return on being the marketing leader with reliable data.</p>
				
				<div style="display: grid; gap: 40px; margin: 40px 0; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));">
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; text-align: center;">
						<h3>Budget Security</h3>
						<p style="font-size: 1.5rem; color: #7cd3d2; font-weight: 700; margin: 15px 0;">Prove ROI</p>
						<p>Marketing budgets with clear attribution data are 3x less likely to get cut during downturns.</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; text-align: center;">
						<h3>Executive Trust</h3>
						<p style="font-size: 1.5rem; color: #7cd3d2; font-weight: 700; margin: 15px 0;">Build Credibility</p>
						<p>Present numbers that leadership actually believes. No more defensive meetings about marketing performance.</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="background: white; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; text-align: center;">
						<h3>Strategic Impact</h3>
						<p style="font-size: 1.5rem; color: #7cd3d2; font-weight: 700; margin: 15px 0;">Drive Growth</p>
						<p>Make marketing decisions that actually improve business performance, not just vanity metrics.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				
				<div style="text-align: center; background: #333; color: white; padding: 40px; border-radius: 8px; margin-top: 40px;">
					<p style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 20px;">The cost of unreliable attribution:</p>
					<p style="font-size: 2rem; color: #eed36b; font-weight: 700;">Your credibility, your budget, and eventually your job.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Implementation Section -->
		<section class="section">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>How This Works (Without Disrupting Your Stack)</h2>
				<p>You don't need to rip and replace anything. This sits alongside your existing tools and gives you the complete picture.</p>
				
				<div style="display: grid; gap: 30px; margin: 40px 0;">
					<div style="display: flex; gap: 20px; align-items: center;">
						<div style="background: #7cd3d2; color: white; width: 40px; height: 40px; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0;">1</div>
						<div>
							<h3>Integration (30 minutes)</h3>
							<p>We connect to your existing tools: CRM, analytics, ad platforms. Nothing gets turned off or changed.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<div style="display: flex; gap: 20px; align-items: center;">
						<div style="background: #7cd3d2; color: white; width: 40px; height: 40px; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0;">2</div>
						<div>
							<h3>Data Unification (48 hours)</h3>
							<p>Our system starts capturing the complete customer journey and reconciling all revenue sources.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<div style="display: flex; gap: 20px; align-items: center;">
						<div style="background: #7cd3d2; color: white; width: 40px; height: 40px; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0;">3</div>
						<div>
							<h3>Boardroom Reports (Day 3)</h3>
							<p>Clean, auditable attribution reports that show exactly which marketing drives revenue.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				
				<div style="text-align: center; background: #f8f9fa; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; margin-top: 40px;">
					<p style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600;">Total disruption to your current workflow: Zero.</p>
					<p>Total improvement to your data confidence: Everything.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- CTA Section -->
		<section class="hero">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>Ready to Present Data You Can Actually Defend?</h2>
				<p>Free attribution audit for marketing leaders. We'll analyze your current setup and show you exactly what you're missing.</p>
				<p>If we can't find significant attribution gaps, the audit is free.</p>
				<a href="/contact" class="btn">Get Your Free Executive Audit</a>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- FAQ Section -->
		<section class="section">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>Questions From Marketing Leaders</h2>
				
				<div style="display: grid; gap: 30px; margin-top: 40px;">
					<div style="padding: 25px; background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2; margin-bottom: 10px;">"Will this replace our current analytics setup?"</h3>
						<p>No. This enhances what you already have by filling in the attribution gaps that platforms like GA4 and Facebook can't see. You keep everything you're currently using.</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="padding: 25px; background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2; margin-bottom: 10px;">"How quickly can we see results?"</h3>
						<p>Data starts flowing immediately. Complete attribution picture in 7 days. First boardroom-ready report available within 2 weeks of implementation.</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="padding: 25px; background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2; margin-bottom: 10px;">"Do we need technical resources to manage this?"</h3>
						<p>No. We handle the technical setup and maintenance. You get clean reports. Your team focuses on strategy, not data wrangling.</p>
					</div>
					
					<div style="padding: 25px; background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px;">
						<h3 style="color: #7cd3d2; margin-bottom: 10px;">"What if our finance team has questions about the data?"</h3>
						<p>We provide full documentation and audit trails for every attribution model. Finance teams love our reporting because it ties directly to actual revenue.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Final Executive Section -->
		<section class="section section-alt">
			<div class="container" style="text-align: center;">
				<h2>The Marketing Leader You Want to Be</h2>
				<p>Six months from now, you're presenting attribution data that makes perfect sense. Every channel's ROI is clear. Every budget decision is data-driven. Finance trusts your numbers. The CEO asks for your input on growth strategy.</p>
				
				<div style="margin: 40px 0;">
					<p style="font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.8;">• No more defending marketing budgets with fuzzy math</p>
					<p style="font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.8;">• No more spending hours reconciling conflicting reports</p>
					<p style="font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.8;">• No more guessing which channels deserve more investment</p>
					<p style="font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.8;">• No more anxiety about board meetings</p>
				</div>
				
				<p style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; margin: 40px 0;">That's what proper attribution does for your career.</p>
				<a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top: 20px;">Get Your Executive Attribution Audit</a>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>